Preview
by GLP-1-MK801 to exert metabolic regu-
lation? What is the metabolic role of
NMDAR-mediated neurotransmission in
GLP-1R-expressing and -non-expressing
cells, and could the role be different in the
hypothalamus vs. dorsal vagal complex?
Also, is glutamatergic extrasynaptic orsyn-
aptic NMDAR-mediated neurotransmis-
sion involved in GLP-1-MK801 action, as
these various transmissions have different
roles in energy balance?10 Answering
these questions would be crucial to opti-
mize and balance the metabolic effects of
GLP-1R and NMDAR in the hypothalamus
and the dorsal vagal complex (Figure 1).
In conclusion, given that a limitation of
several incretin-based anti-obesity thera-
pies is a body weight rebound following
treatment discontinuation, the GLP-1-
MK801 conjugate, which may alter synap-
tic plasticity, may one day prove to
yield more long-lasting neural adaptations
such
that
lifelong
drug
dependence
may be circumvented. Additionally, unlike
typical caloric restriction, which is coun-
tered by the brain by lowering metabolic
rate,
GLP-1-MK801
maintains
energy
expenditure at rates similar to vehicle
controls, at least in rodent models, over
a 10-day time frame. Thus, evaluation of
this pharmaceutical intervention in a clin-
ical setting for longer durations is war-
ranted. The achievement of lasting weight
loss in obesity is a formidable task. Devel-
opments in this area of research are crit-
ical to help combat this disease.
